t%3Btheoretically%26quot%3B%20prevent%20infection%2C%20it%20won't%20completely%20rule%20out%20chances%20of%20one%20developing.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bite%20itself%20is%20the%20issue%20as%20you%20are%20pushing%20oral%20bacteria%20and%20whatever%20else%20through%20the%20skin%20barrier%2C%26quot%3B%20Friedman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22848%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mary%20Minahan%20is%20a%20tattoo%20artist%20with%20over%20a%20decade%20of%20experience%20in%20the%20industry.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656623a7fe5bc6545ebcf98e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221274%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMary%20Minahan%20is%20a%20tattoo%20artist%20with%20over%20a%20decade%20of%20experience%20in%20the%20industry.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Mary%20Minahan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Friedman%2C%20human%20saliva%20is%20known%20to%20contain%20as%20many%20as%2050%20species%20of%20bacteria%2C%20which%20is%20why%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhy-mouth-bacteria-can-cause-a-flesh-eating-infection-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehuman%20bites%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20believed%20to%20cause%20higher%20rates%20of%20infection%20than%20other%20types%20of%20injuries.%20Risks%20include%20the%20potential%20for%20infections%20caused%20by%20bacteria%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFriedman%20also%20said%20that%20there%20have%20been%20reports%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fman-necrotizing-fasciitis-bitten-by-family-member-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehuman%20bites%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecan%20lead%20to%20the%20transfer%20of%20viruses%20like%20hepatitis%2C%C2%A0herpes%20virus%2C%20tetanus%2C%20and%20syphilis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%20infection%2C%20Friedman%20said%20tattooing%20over%20a%20bite%20could%20influence%20the%20appearance%20of%20the%20ink%20%26quot%3Bat%20minimum%26quot%3B%20but%20could%20also%20%26quot%3Bresult%20in