20up%20from%201%2C841k.%20There%20have%20been%20questions%20over%20seasonal%20adjustment%20issues%20and%20data%20volatility%2C%20but%20the%20trend%20is%20certainly%20towards%20higher%20continuing%20claims%20while%20initial%20claims%20remain%20low.%20Essentially%2C%20the%20message%20is%20that%20firms%20are%20reluctant%20to%20fire%20workers%2C%20but%20they%20are%20less%20inclined%20to%20hire%20new%20workers.%20i.e.%20more%20evidence%20of%20a%20cooling%2C%20but%20not%20collapsing%2C%20labour%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20Knightley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20consumer%20spending%2C%20while%20solid%2C%20faces%20a%20tougher%20road%20ahead%20in%202024%20as%20real%20household%20disposable%20incomes%20shows%20signs%20of%20weakness%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcredit-card-debt-recession-warning-us-economy-outlook-wells-fargo-2023-8%5C%22%3Ecredit%20card%20delinquencies%20rise%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20student%20load%20payments%20add%20further%20strain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20data%20suggests%20stagnant%20real%20household%20incomes%20over%20quite%20some%20time%20now.%20So%20far%2C%20this%20has%20been%20offset%20by%20the%20running%20down%20of%20savings%20and%20the%20use%20of%20debt%20to%20fuel%20spending%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20Knightley%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20tighter%20credit%20conditions%20and%20high%20borrowing%20costs%20are%20likely%20to%20weigh%20heavily%20on%20the%20flow%20of%20credit%20to%20the%20household%20sector%20while%20there%20is%20growing%20evidence%20of%20pandemic-era%20accrued%20excess%20savings%20being%20exhausted%20for%20an%20increasing%20number%20of%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Knightley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20all%20chalks%20up%20to%20an%20economy%20that%20is%20on%20thin%20ice%2C%20but%20hasn't%20broken%20yet.%20And%20it%20might%20not%20break%20if%20the%20Fed%20can%20successfully%20ease%20interest%20rates%20lower%20before%20the%20economy%20enters%20a%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOtherwise%2C%20a%20broken%20economy%20likely%20means%20that%20the%20Fed%20won't%20be%20so%20patient%20with%20cutting%20interest%20rates.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-rate-cuts-forecast-2024-full-accommodation-economic-contraction-unemployment-2023-11%5C%22%3EUBS%20expects%20the%20Fed%20to%20cut%20interest%20rates%20by%20a%20whopping%20275%20basis%20points%20next%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20response%20to%20a%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomy-slowdown-interest-rates-outlook-federal-reserve-cuts-next-year-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701373127000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6568d83058e7c0c29a28688d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomy-slowdown-interest-rates-outlook-federal-reserve-cuts-next-year-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20forecasted%20interest%20rate%20cuts%20would%20bring%20the%20effective%20Federal%20Funds%20rate%20to%20about%203.83%25%20at%20the%20end%20of%202024.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mfox%40businessinsider.com%20(Matthew%20Fox)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A25%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomy-slowdown-interest-rates-outlook-federal-reserve-cuts-next-year-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Here's%20how%20the%202024%20election%20could%20impact%20the%20status%20of%20the%20dollar%20versus%20another%20big%20rival%20currency%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224284%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Joe%20Biden%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6568d14e58e7c0c29a286139%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222142%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJoe%20Biden.%3Cp%3EDrew%20Angerer%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EJapan's%20yen%20could%