A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fgadgets-news%2Fwhatsapp-introduces-secret-code-for-chats-what-it-is-how-it-works-and-more%2Farticleshow%2F105629265.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22WhatsApp%20introduces%20secret%20code%20feature%20for%20Chat%20Lock%2C%20enhancing%20user%20privacy.%20The%20unique%20password%20adds%20an%20extra%20layer%20of%20protection%20to%20locked%20chats%2C%20separate%20from%20the%20phone%20unlock%20password.%20Users%20can%20choose%20to%20hide%20the%20Locked%20Chats%20folder%20and%20reveal%20it%20only%20by%20typing%20the%20secret%20code%20in%20the%20search%20bar.%20WhatsApp%20plans%20to%20roll%20out%20the%20feature%20globally%20in%20the%20coming%20months%2C%20aiming%20to%20provide%20more%20functions%20for%20privacy%20protection.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fgadgets-news%2Fwhatsapp-introduces-secret-code-for-chats-what-it-is-how-it-works-and-more%2Farticleshow%2F105629265.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Attempt%20to%20murder%3A%20Monu%20Manesar%20appears%20in%20court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701355575000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105632466%2Cimgsize-15326.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fgurgaon%2Fcow-vigilante-monu-manesar-appears-in-court-in-attempt-to-murder-case%2Farticleshow%2F105632490.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20first%20hearing%20in%20the%20case%20was%20convened%20by%20additional%20sessions%20judge%20Jasbir%20Singh%20after%20it%20was%20transferred%20from%20Pataudi%20to%20the%20Gurgaon%20sessions%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fgurgaon%2Fcow-vigilante-monu-manesar-appears-in-court-in-attempt-to-murder-case%2Farticleshow%2F105632490.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20The%20Long%2C%20Agonising%20Adoption%20Process%20In%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20three%20crore%20orphaned%20children%20in%20India%2C%20but%20only%203%2C500%20to%204%2C000%20children%20are%20available%20for%20adoption%20in%20a%20year%20and%20some%2030%2C000%20prospective%20parents%20have%20to%20wait%20for%20three%20years%20to%20bring%20home%20a%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaking%20note%20of%20this%20discrepancy%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20observed%20recently%3A%20%26quot%3BWhy%20are%20they%20(Central%20Adoption%20Resource%20Authority)%20stalling%20adoptions%3F%20Why%20is%20CARA%20not%20doing%20it%3F%20Hundreds%20of%20children%20are%20awaiting%20adoption%20in%20the%20hope%20of%20a%20better%20life.%26quot%3B%20The%20remarks%20were%20made%20when%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20hearing%20two%20petitions%20flagging%20gaps%20that%20were%20delaying%20adoptions%20and%20making%20the%20entire%20process%20a%20sham.%20The%20practical%20difficulties%20of%20adoption%20were%20also%20highlighted%20in%20the%20court%2C%20with%20one%20of%20the%20judges%20bringing%20out%20the%20humane%20and%20human%20aspect%20and%20cost%20to%20the%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECARA%2C%20a%20statutory%20body%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Women%20and%20Child%20Development%2C%20functions%20as%20the%20central%20body%20for%20adoption%20of%20Indian%20children%20and%20is%20mandated%20to%20monitor%20and%20regulate%20in-country%20and%20inter-country%20adoptions.%20CARA%20primarily%20deals%20with%20the%20adoption%20of%20%26quot%3Borphan%2C%20abandoned%20and%20surrendered%26quot%3B%20children%20through%20its%20associated%20and%20recognised%20adoption%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20red%20tape%20and%20lack%20of%20transparency%2C%20several%20thousand%20children%20are%20being%20deprived%20of%20home%20and%20the%20love%20of%20parents.%20With%20each%20month's%20delay%2C%20the%20children%20grow%20and%20age%2C%20and%20their%20chances%20of%20adoptability%20and%20adaptability%20diminishes.%20The%20prospective%20parents%2C%20too%2C%20lose%20their%20precious%20years%20doing%20cumbersome%20and%20complicated%20paperwork.%20Their%20financial%20condition%20suffers%20as%20they%20scout%20and%20wait%20their%20turn%20and%20are%20made%20to%20visit%20different%20adoption%20centres%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20conditions%20of%20the%20shelter%20homes%20where%20these%20children%20are%20placed%20are%20also%20not%20hygienic%2C%20with%20funds%20and%20staff%20both%20short.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeepak%20Sharma%2C%20Trustee%2C%20Udayan%20Care%2C%20an%20NGO%20for%20Child%20Rights%2C%20says%20there%20is%20no%20dearth%20of%20funds%20for%20his%20organisation%20but%20some%20shelters%20in%20India%20face%20financial%20challenges%20due%20to%20their%20location%20and%20the%20resources%20available.%20%26quot%3BFunding%20comes%20from%20a%20combination%20of%20sources.%20There%20is%20government%20funding%20in%20Mission%20Vatsalya%20for%20funding%20institutions%2C%20mostly%20funds%20come%20from%20donations%20from%20individuals%2C%20corporations%2C%20and%20other%20charitable%20entities%20or%20even%20from%20international%20organisations%20and%20foundations%20or%20corporate%20social%20responsibility%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Sharma%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20adoptions%20are%20governed%20by%20two%20laws%20-%20the%20Hindu%20Adoption%20and%20Maintenance%20Act%2C%201956%20(HAMA)%20and%20the%20Juvenile%20Justice%20(JJ)%20Act%2C%202015.%20Both%20laws%20have%20their%20separate%20eligibility%20criteria%20for%20adoptive%20parents.%20Those%20applying%20under%20the%20Juvenile%20Justice%20Act%20need%20to%20register%20on%20CARA's%20portal%2C%20after%20which%20a%20specialised%20adoption%20agency%20carries%20out%20a%20home%20study%20report.%20When%20it%20finds%20the%20candidate%20eligible%20for%20adoption%2C%20a%20child%20declared%20legally%20free%20for%20adoption%20is%20referred%20to%20the%20applicant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20HAMA%2C%20a%20court%20order%2C%20'dattaka%20hom'%20ceremony%20or%20an%20adoption%20deed%20is%20sufficient%20to%20obtain%20irrevocable%20adoption%20rights.%20Hindus%2C%20Buddhists%2C%20Jains%2C%20and%20Sikhs%20are%20legalised%20to%20adopt%20kids%20under%20HAMA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECARA%20carries%20out%20the%20tedious%20process%20to%20safeguard%20adoptive%20children%20from%20abuse%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20adoptive%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Parliament%20passed%20the%20Juvenile%20Justice%20(Care%20and%20Protection%20of%20Children)%202021%2C%20in%20order%20to%20amend%20the%20JJ%20Act%2C%202015.%20The%20crucial%20changes%20include%20authorising%20District%20Magistrates%20(DMs)%20and%20Additional%20District%20Magistrates%20to%20issue%20adoption%20orders%20under%20Section%2061%20of%20the%20JJ%20Act%20by%20striking%20out%20the%20word%20'court'.%20These%20changes%20were%20carried%20out%20%26quot%3Bin%20order%20to%20ensure%20speedy%20disposal%20of%20cases%20and%20enhance%20accountability%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20the%20government%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20very%20purpose%20of%20these%20amendments%20has%20not%20been%20met%20as%20no%20time%20limit%20has%20been%20set%20up%20for%20the%20transfer%20of%20all%20pending%20adoption%20cases%20before%20the%20courts%20to%20the%20District%20Magistrates%2C%20which%20may%20end%20up%20in%20longer%20delays.%20Moreover%2C%20prospective%20parents%20are%20also%20not%20clear%20about%20the%20legality%20of%20an%20executive%20order%20on%20the%20adopted%20child's%20entitlements%20on%20succession%20and%20inheritance%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202022%2C%20a%20parliamentary%20standing%20committee%20had%20expressed%20serious%20concerns%20over%20the%20decline%20in%20the%20number%20of%20children%20coming%20to%20adoption%20agencies%20over%20the%20years%2C%20saying%20it%20pointed%20to%20trafficking%20or%20a%20thriving%20illegal%20child%20adoption%20market.%20It's%20a%20fact%20that%20many%20unregistered%20adoption%20agencies%20are%20flourishing%20in%20the%20country%3B%20illegal%20and%20unregulated%20adoptions%20are%20being%20carried%20out.%20Some%20are%20involved%20in%20child%20trafficking%20or%20exploiting%20vulnerable%20children%20and%20their%20biological%20and%20adoptive%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20there%20is%20a%20shorter%20queue%20for%20older%20children%2C%20children%20with%20special%20needs%2C%20or%20sometimes%2C%20even%20children%20from%20some%20regions.%20CARA%20has%20even%20introduced%20a%20new%20category%20of%20%26quot%3BChildren%20for%20Immediate%20Placement%26quot%3B%20where%20the%20wait%20time%20may%20be%20considerably%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Sharma%20says%20generally%2C%20there%20is%20a%20demand%20for%20newborn%20and%20younger%20children%2C%20particularly%20infants%20and%20toddlers%2C%20in%20the%20adoption%20process.%20%26quot%3BMany%20adoptive%20parents%20prefer%20younger%20children%20as%20they%20desire%20to%20experience%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20a%20child's%20development%20and%20form%20strong%20bonds%20from%20the%20start.%20But%20now%20CARA%20is%20advocating%20for%20adoption%20of%20older%20children%20also%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20young%20single%20woman%20(name%20withheld)%20in%20Bengaluru%20has%20been%20in%20the%20queue%20for%20adoption%20for%20three%20years.%20She%20has%20completed%20all%20the%20paperwork%2C%20but%20her%20wait%20has%20been%20stretched%20by%20the%20adoption%20agency%2C%20where%20she%20is%20registered.%20She%20thinks%20that%20her%20adoption%20agency%20is%20giving%20preference%20to%20candidates%20who%20are%20better%20off%20than%20her%20financially.%20%26quot%3BMy%20waiting%20time%20has%20been%20constantly%20increased%20without%20any%20reason.%20The%20counsellors%20are%20also%20of%20little%20help.%20Except%20for%20guiding%20us%20about%20the%20papers%20and%20forms%20to%20be%20filled%2C%20they%20have%20hardly%20been%20of%20any%20assistance%20in%20understanding%20the%20process%20or%20how%20it%20works%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20an%20urgent%20need%20to%20streamline%20the%20adoption%20process%2C%20simplify%20paperwork%2C%20transparency%2C%20and%20reduce%20the%20time%20limit%2C%20to%20the%20benefit%20of%20both%20the%20child%20and%20the%20adoptive%20parents.%20Loopholes%2C%20doubts%2C%20and%20ambiguities%20in%20current%20legislation%20must%20be%20plugged.%20Unless%20this%20happens%2C%20thousands%20of%20children%20will%20languish%20in%20shelter%20homes%20bereft%20of%20love%2C%20care%20and%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Bharti%20Mishra%20Nath%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701355440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F1pac1sgo_adoption-baby_625x300_21_July_18.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-long-agonising-adoption-process-in-india-4622213%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20are%20three%20crore%20orphaned%20children%20in%20India%2C%20but%20only%203%2C500%20to%204%2C000%20children%20are%20available%20for%20adoption%20in%20a%20year%20and%20some%2030%2C000%20prospective%20parents%20have%20to%20wait%20for%20three%20years%20to%20bring%20home%20a%20child.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-long-agonising-adoption-process-in-india-4622213%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-long-agonising-adoption-process-in-india-4622213%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-long-agonising-adoption-process-in-india-4622213%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NCLT%20has%20power%20to%20decide%20IBC%20disputes%2C%20not%20HC%3A%20Go%20First%20RP%20to%20Delhi%20