al%20Family%20Health%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMarital%20rape%20already%20has%20civil%20remedies%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F15436%2F1%2Fprotection_of_women_from_domestic_violence_act%252C_2005.pdf%5C%22%3EProtection%20of%20Women%20from%20Domestic%20Violence%20Act%20(PWDVA)%202005%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0under%20the%20concept%20of%20sexual%20violence%20as%20a%20form%20of%20domestic%20violence%2C%20as%20well%20as%20in%20matrimonial%20law%2C%20which%20allows%20for%20divorce%20and%20judicial%20separation%20on%20the%20ground%20of%20%E2%80%98cruelty%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20criminal%20law%20provision%20on%20rape%20has%20an%20exception%20for%20husbands.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fshow-data%3Factid%3DAC_CEN_5_23_00037_186045_1523266765688%26orderno%3D424%5C%22%3EException%202%20to%20Section%20375%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%3C%2Fa%3E%20states%3A%20%E2%80%9CSexual%20intercourse%20or%20sexual%20acts%20by%20a%20man%20with%20his%20own%20wife%20%E2%80%A6is%20not%20rape.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20provision%20(Section%20376B%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code)%20makes%20a%20husband%E2%80%99s%20rape%20of%20his%20wife%20who%20has%20separated%20from%20him%20a%20criminal%20offence%20punishable%20with%20a%20lesser%20penalty%20than%20in%20other%20cases%20of%20rape.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Findia-marital-rape-criminal-law%5C%22%3EWhy%20Is%20Outlawing%20Marital%20Rape%20Still%20a%20Distant%20Dream%20in%20India%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20provisions%20are%20remnants%20of%20British%20colonial%20law%20that%20reflect%20the%20then-existing%20English%20legal%20standard.%20While%20the%20marital%20rape%20exemption%20was%20overturned%20in%20England%20in%201991%20through%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvlex.co.uk%2Fvid%2Fr-v-r-1991-792746197%5C%22%3Ejudgment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20India%20is%20still%20grappling%20with%20the%20ramifications%20of%20the%20exemption%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20provisions%20reinforce%20and%20embed%20in%20law%20the%20notion%20of%20a%20husband%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98ownership%E2%80%99%20of%20his%20wife%E2%80%99s%20person%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20incongruent%20with%20the%20Indian%20constitutional%20guarantee%20to%20all%20of%20right%20to%20life%2C%20dignity%2C%20equality%20and%20non-discrimination%20on%20grounds%20including%20sex.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202022%2C%20a%20two-judge%20Division%20Bench%20of%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20delivered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2Fras11052022cw2842015190346-417219.pdf%5C%22%3Ea%20split%20judgment%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0with%20one%20judge%20striking%20down%20the%20marital%20rape%20exemption%20as%20unconstitutional%2C%20and%20the%20other%20upholding%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%20exemption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judicial%20reasonings%20for%20the%20findings%20contrast%20starkly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Rajiv%20Shakdher%20found%20that%20the%20marital%20rape%20exception%20violates%20provisions%20of%20the%20Indian%20constitution%20as%20it%20leads%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdenial%20of%20bodily%20autonomy%20and%20agency%20of%20married%20women%2C%20which%20must%20be%20rectified%E2%80%9D.%20He%20further%20observed%20that%20the%20marital%20rape%20exemption%20%E2%80%9Csuffers%20from%20manifest%20arbitrariness%20and%20discrimination%20as%20a%20crime%20as%20heinous%20as%20rape%20is%20not%20recognised%20as%20an%20offence%20in%20marriage%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Hari%20Shankar%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20wrote%20that%20within%20a%20marriage%2C%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccut%20and%20dry%E2%80%9D%20approach%20cannot%20be%20adopted.%20He%20argued%20that%2C%20often%2C%20consent%20is%20given%20for%20sexual%20intimacy%20though%20will%20may%20not%20exist%2C%20and%20the%20state%20does%20not%20have%20the%20right%20to%20interfere%20in%20the%20private%20space%20within%20a%20marital%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20reasoning%20resonates%20with%20a%20much-criticised%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F191703%2F%5C%22%3Ejudgment%20of%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20in%201984%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20it%20was%20stated%20that%20%E2%80%9Cintroduction%20of%20constitutional%20law%20in%20the%20home%20is%20most%20inappropriate.%20It%20is%20like%20introducing%20a%20bull%20in%20a%20china%20shop.%20It%20will%20prove%20to%20be%20a%20ruthless%20destroyer%20of%20the%20marriage%20institution%20and%20all%20that%20it%20stands%20for%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20water%20has%20flown%20under%20the%20bridge%20since%20the%201990s%20when%20feminist%20scholarship%20analysed%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fegyankosh.ac.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F3492%2F1%2FMWG-002-B1-U4.pdf%5C%22%3Epublic-private%20dichotomy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20drawing%20attention%20to%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20domestic%20sphere%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20a%20primary%20site%20of%20inequality%20for%20women%20%E2%80%93%20was%20kept%20shielded%20from%20regulation%20by%20law%20and%20policy%20that%20may%20protect%20and%20promote%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20of%20privacy%20in%20law%20is%20often%20a%20double-edged%20sword%20for%20women.%20When%20associated%20with%20individual%20dignity%2C%20bodily%20integrity%2C%20and%20sexual%20autonomy%2C%20it%20can%20be%20a%20tool%20for%20women%20to%20assert%20their%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20the%20privacy%20of%20the%20family%20seeks%20protection%20from%20%E2%80%98external%20interference%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20including%20of%20law%20%E2%80%93%20it%20can%20potentially%20harm%20the%20rights%20of%20women%2C%20especially%20given%20gendered%20power%20dynamics%20within%20the%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20several%20instances%2C%20state%20responsibility%20has%20already%20countered%20the%20public-private%20dichotomy%20to%20protect%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%3A%20Enacting%20section%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fshow-data%3Factid%3DAC_CEN_5_23_00037_186045_1523266765688%26orderno%3D562%5C%22%3E%C2%A0498A%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20defines%20and%20punishes%20cruelty%20on%20a%20wife%20by%20husband%20and%20his%20relatives%20as%20well%20as%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F15436%2F1%2Fprotection_of_women_from_domestic_violence_act%252C_2005.pdf%5C%22%3EProtection%20of%20Women%20from%20Domestic%20Violence%20Act%20(PWDVA)%2C%202005%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F5556%2F1%2Fdowry_prohibition.pdf%5C%22%3EDowry%20Prohibition%20Act%201961%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0are%20good%20examples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20convey%20a%20clear%2C%20unequivocal%20message%20that%20the%20domestic%20sphere%20is%20an%20important%20sphere%20for%20legal%20intervention%2C%20as%20power%20dynamics%20in%20the%20home%20can%20be%20exploited%20by%20the%20powerholders%20to%20perpetuate%20violence%20and%20discrimination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20sense%2C%20the%20patriarchal%20myth%20of%20home%20as%20a%20safe%20space%20for%20all%20is%20busted.%20Justice%20Hari%20Shankar%E2%80%99s%20observations%20that%20the%20state%20has%20no%20right%20to%20interfere%20in%20the%20privacy%20of%20a%20marital%20relationship%20fly%20in%20the%20face%20of%20current%20legal%20thinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20critics%20argue%20removing%20the%20marital%20rape%20exemption%20could%20undermine%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Justice%20Verma%20Committee%20famously%20recommended%20removing%20the%20marital%20rape%20exemption%20in%20its%202013%20report%20into%20how%20India%E2%80%99s%20criminal%20system%20could%20better%20deal%20with%20sexual%20violence.%20However%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbills_acts%2Fbills_parliament%2F2012%2FSCR_Criminal_Law_Bill.pdf%5C%22%3EParliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Home%20Affairs%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0rejected%20that%20recommendation%2C%20concluding%20that%20if%20marital%20rape%20were%20criminalised%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fmarital-rape-brought-under-law-will-put-family-system-under-stress%2Fstory-9lX7c5KoFPgbzFot5DK1iL.html%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cthe%20entire%20family%20system%20will%20be%20under%20great%20stress%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20the%20Union%20Minister%20for%20Women%20and%20Child%20Development%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Fmaneka-gandhi-marital-rape-criminalisation-312848-2016-03-11%5C%22%3Eargued%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20there%20could%20not%20be%20a%20law%20against%20marital%20rape%20because%20marriage%20was%20a%20%E2%80%98sacrament%E2%80%99%20and%20due%20to%20factors%20such%20as%20poverty%2C%20illiteracy%20and%20religious%20beliefs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%202022%20proceedings%20before%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%2C%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20witnessed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Fopinion%2Fpov%2Fmen-on-marriage-strike-against-marital-rape-laws-some-people-laugh-say-good-riddance%2F808285%2F%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98marriage%20strike%E2%80%99%20by%20men%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20counter%20to%20a%20possible%20move%20to%20delete%20the%20marital%20rape%20exemption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20felt%20entitled%20to%20rape%20their%20wife%20in%20marriage%2C%20and%20were%20ready%20to%20boycott%20marriage%20if%20the%20licence%20to%20rape%20was%20deleted.%20Women%20responded%20with%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fmay-marriagestrike-remain-for-centuries-indian-women-respond-to-twitter-trend%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98May%20%23Marriage%20Strike%20Remain%20for%20Centuries%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20polarisation%20focused%20on%20the%20bodily%20autonomy%20and%20sexual%20integrity%20of%20married%20women%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20their%20husbands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeleting%20the%20marital%20rape%20exemption%20would%20create%20a%20normative%20standard%20of%20acceptable%20behaviour%20within%20a%20marriage%2C%20in%20line%20with%20the%20Indian%20constitutional%20guarantee%20of%20fundamental%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20my%20own%20research%20points%20to%20the%20need%20for%20law%20to%20treat%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage%20as%20one%20with%20mutual%20love%2C%20care%2C%20and%20companionship%20as%20its%20foundations%2C%20rather%20than%20coercion%20and%20violence.%20As%20a%20logical%20corollary%2C%20the%20marital%20rape%20exemption%20breeds%20coercion%20and%20violence%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20sanctity%20of%20marriage%20and%20warrants%20deletion%20from%20the%20statute%20books.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3ESaumya%20Uma%20is%20a%20Professor%20of%20Law%20and%20Director%2C%20Centre%20for%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Rights%2C%20Jindal%20Global%20Law%20School%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20She%20researches%2C%20writes%2C%20and%20teaches%20at%20the%20intersections%20of%20human%20rights%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20the%20law.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20first%20appeared%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%2Fabout-us%2F%5C%22%3E360info%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Cem%3ERead%20the%20original%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%2Fwomens-rights-in-the-balance-as-india-weighs-criminalising-marital-rape%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701330612000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F10%2F26184133%2Fmarriage-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhy-the-marital-rape-exemption-in-criminal-law-must-go%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20poised%20to%20deliver%20a%20landmark%20judgement%20that%20may%20make%